      <text>2.1.3 (Obtaining Linear Factors)</text>
    </name>
    <questiontext format="moodle_auto_format">
      <text><![CDATA[<p>Write the polynomial \(P(x) ={@qq1@}\) as a product of linear factors.</p>

<p>[[input:ans1]] [[validation:ans1]]</p>]]></text>
    </questiontext>
    <generalfeedback format="moodle_auto_format">
      <text><![CDATA[<p>Recall that a linear factor is a factor of the form \(x - a\). We already have that the factor \((x + {@aa@})\) is a linear factor. So it remains to factorise the quadratic factor \({@expand((x+bb)*(x-cc))@}\). We see that 
\[
{@expand((x+bb)*(x-cc))@} = (x+{@bb@})(x-{@cc@}).
\]
Therefore \(P(x) = {@ta1@}\)]]></text>
    </generalfeedback>
